# TextGenDemoSystem

## Purpose
SandboxApp text-generation demo panel (ImGui). Returns early until the engine TextGen singletons exist
(created lazily by TextGenSystem), then lazily creates its editable state singleton. Each frame it draws
an ImGui window with a prompt box, temperature + max-tokens controls, and a **Generate** button. Pressing
Generate (only when no job is running) emits a single GenerateTextRequest carrying the prompt + config,
targeting `k_TextGenTargetID`. While a job runs the button is disabled and a busy note is shown; the
latest completion (read from TextGenResultSingletonComponent by the target UUID) is displayed below.
Every ImGui call is guarded so the headless test build (no ImGui context) is a no-op, like the other
debug panels.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| TextGenJobSingletonComponent | read | Busy state — disables the button while a generation runs |
| TextGenResultSingletonComponent | read | The generated text to display, looked up by `k_TextGenTargetID` |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| TextGenDemoStateSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; holds the editable prompt buffer + temperature + max tokens |
| GenerateTextRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | The text-generation request (engine-typed), read by the engine TextGenSystem |
